### PostgREST Read API examples against the demo model.
### Calls PostgREST directly (port 3000) — no authentication required
### (runs as api_anon which inherits authz_reader).
### Requires: docker compose up (bootstrap.sh)
### Select the "dev" environment to use the variables below.

### =====================================================================
### SINGLE ACCESS CHECK (check_access)
### =====================================================================

### Alice can read the payroll document (via payroll_team membership)
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: true

###

### Alice cannot read the tax document (wrong team)
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_tax_001"
}
### Expected: false

###

### Bob (advisor) can read payroll doc via internal_collaborator
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "bob",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: true

###

### Carol (client user) can read client-space doc but cannot edit
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "client_user",
  "p_user_id": "carol",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_client_001"
}
### Expected: true

###

POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "client_user",
  "p_user_id": "carol",
  "p_relation": "can_edit",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_client_001"
}
### Expected: false

###

### =====================================================================
### ACCESS CHECK WITH CONTEXT (conditions / ABAC)
### =====================================================================

### Time-based condition: check within the grant window
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_with_context
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "viewer",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_temp_001",
  "context": { "current_time": "2026-03-11T10:00:00Z" }
}
### Expected: true (within the 2-hour grant window)

###

### Time-based condition: check outside the grant window
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_with_context
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "viewer",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_temp_001",
  "context": { "current_time": "2026-03-11T12:00:00Z" }
}
### Expected: false (after the 2-hour window)

###

### =====================================================================
### CONTEXTUAL TUPLES (JSONB)
### =====================================================================

### Frank has no stored tuple — access denied
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "frank",
  "p_relation": "viewer",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_client_001"
}
### Expected: false

###

### With a contextual tuple — access granted for this request only
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_with_contextual_tuples_jsonb
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "frank",
  "p_relation": "viewer",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_client_001",
  "context": null,
  "contextual_tuples": [
    {
      "user_type": "internal_user",
      "user_id": "frank",
      "relation": "viewer",
      "object_type": "document",
      "object_id": "doc_client_001"
    }
  ]
}
### Expected: true (contextual tuple is not persisted)

###

### =====================================================================
### BATCH ACCESS CHECK — check_access_batch (returns JSONB array)
### =====================================================================

### Check multiple permissions in a single call
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_checks": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "can_read",   "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "can_edit",   "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "can_read",   "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_tax_001" }
  ]
}
### Expected: [{"decision":true},{"decision":true},{"decision":false}]

###

### Batch with deny_on_first_deny — stops at first false
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_checks": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_acc_001" }
  ],
  "p_semantic": "deny_on_first_deny"
}
### Expected: [{"decision":false},{"decision":null}]

###

### Batch with permit_on_first_permit — stops at first true
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_batch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_checks": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_acc_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_tax_001" }
  ],
  "p_semantic": "permit_on_first_permit"
}
### Expected: [{"decision":false},{"decision":true},{"decision":null}]

###

### =====================================================================
### BATCH ACCESS CHECK — check_access_batch_typed_jsonb (returns rows)
### =====================================================================
### Returns rows with user_type, user_id, relation, object_type,
### object_id, decision — useful when you need to correlate results
### with inputs without relying on array ordering.

### Mixed users and permissions
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_batch_typed_jsonb
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_checks": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "can_read",  "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "alice", "relation": "can_edit",  "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva",   "relation": "can_read",  "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "client_user",   "user_id": "carol", "relation": "can_read",  "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_client_001" }
  ]
}
### Expected: array of objects, each with all input fields + decision
### alice/can_read → true, alice/can_edit → true, eva/can_read → false, carol/can_read → true

###

### Typed batch with deny_on_first_deny
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/check_access_batch_typed_jsonb
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_checks": [
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_payroll_001" },
    { "user_type": "internal_user", "user_id": "eva", "relation": "can_read", "object_type": "document", "object_id": "doc_acc_001" }
  ],
  "p_semantic": "deny_on_first_deny"
}
### Expected: first row decision=false, second row decision=null (short-circuited)

###

### =====================================================================
### LIST OBJECTS — "Which resources can user X access?"
### =====================================================================

### Which documents can Bob read?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "bob",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document"
}
### Expected: [{"object_id":"doc_acc_001"},{"object_id":"doc_payroll_001"},{"object_id":"doc_tax_001"}]

###

### With pagination — first page
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "bob",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_limit": 2,
  "p_offset": 0
}
### Expected: 2 results

###

### With pagination — second page
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "bob",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_limit": 2,
  "p_offset": 2
}
### Expected: 1 result (last page)

###

### Which documents can Carol (client user) read?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_objects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "client_user",
  "p_user_id": "carol",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document"
}
### Expected: doc_client_001, doc_client_002, doc_client_private_001

###

### =====================================================================
### LIST SUBJECTS — "Who can access resource Z?"
### =====================================================================

### Which internal users can read the payroll document?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_subjects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_subject_type": "internal_user",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: [{"subject_id":"alice"},{"subject_id":"bob"},{"subject_id":"julia"}]

###

### Who can edit the payroll document?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_subjects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_subject_type": "internal_user",
  "p_relation": "can_edit",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: [{"subject_id":"alice"},{"subject_id":"bob"}]

###

### =====================================================================
### LIST ACTIONS — "What can user X do on resource Z?"
### =====================================================================

### What can Alice do on the payroll document?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_actions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: [{"action":"can_edit"},{"action":"can_read"}]

###

### What can Carol do on a client-space document?
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/list_actions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "client_user",
  "p_user_id": "carol",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_client_001"
}
### Expected: [{"action":"can_read"}]

###

### =====================================================================
### DIAGNOSTICS — EXPLAIN ACCESS
### =====================================================================

### Full resolution trace showing every rule evaluated
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/explain_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: JSON with {result: true, summary: "...", trace: [...]}

###

### Explain a denied access — see why Eva cannot read payroll doc
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/explain_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "eva",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001"
}
### Expected: JSON with {result: false, summary: "...", trace: [...]}

###

### Explain with only successful paths (less noise)
POST {{postgrest_url}}/rpc/explain_access
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "p_store": "demo",
  "p_user_type": "internal_user",
  "p_user_id": "alice",
  "p_relation": "can_read",
  "p_object_type": "document",
  "p_object_id": "doc_payroll_001",
  "p_successful_only": true
}
### Expected: JSON with only the matching rule paths in the trace
